                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 761.94/113</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Guthrie</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-16T13:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Embassy’s telegram of July 16, 3 p.m. I am confidentially informed that it is
                    understood that there is included in the new Russo-Japanese convention a further
                    clause in which it is provided that after the present war Japanese troops will
                    be permitted largely to replace the Russian troops formerly stationed at
                    Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guthrie</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
